SSRL-BLDO dayshift report 2022-Feb-24
text: Program: Beam to users w/500ma 5min. freq. fill mode. Beam lines: All open except BL17. Faults/Alarms: None this shift. Experiments: Rad samples @ BL11-2, no other concerns expressed. Other: Water leak was reported near BL4-3 messer cabinet. Turns out there is a small leak in the BL4-0 hutch from a quick disconnect that did not fully close when flow check was done. This will be fixed tomorrow during the 0700-0830 down. Also did some machining jobs for BL6-2.

title: FACET 18-2
text: 18-2 k13 Will not reset, sprayed and exercised the contacts, Station on A-OK

title: PEM will turn off 11-2 filament at end of shift tonight in anticipation of a tube swap tomorrow.
Insert VV795 in injector tonight when 11-2 filament is turned off
text: This is out of precaution for tomorrow's work. Turn off the DL10 bend when this happens to run to the straight ahead Faraday cup.

title: Attempting some emittance tuning by scanning BC14 CQs on LI18/19 wire sizes
text: Slow going so far, no obvious correlation between the first quad and the wire sizes. Possible that underlying drift is overwhelming the effect of the quad scan?

title: Attempting some emittance tuning by scanning BC14 CQs on LI18/19 wire sizes
text: Slow going so far, no obvious correlation between the first quad and the wire sizes. Possible that underlying drift is overwhelming the effect of the quad scan?

title: MFX, XPP done. TMO wants to keep this config (6.3 GeV, 870 eV), just at full rate.
Delivering full rate 870 eV to TMO.
Taking back beam from TMO so that we can LEM L3 to soft line energy, hopefully bring down huge jitter and help with stability.
TMO requests gain length measurement
text: They want to know if we are reaching "saturation" before undulator 43 or not. It is still unclear to me if the apparent "saturation" point on the gain length plot is the actual FEL saturation point or not - as I believe we get a huge amount of energy out of the post-saturation taper when we are able to use it. But nobody understands or wants to explain FEL so who knows :(

title: Tuned up beam to ~ 4 mJ, jitter down from over 50% to < 10 %
Pulled first undulator per TMO request.
Adjusting CQs has pushed the losses further downstream -- most beam loss between TORO 2452 and 3163 now.
text: Emittance tuning has had only limited effect, most wire measurements do not reproduce well due to upstream jitter.

title: * Re: beam loss between TORO 2452 and 3163 now. > Trying LI19 quads and BC20 steering to improve transmission
* Re: transmission > got a mostly sub-1mm orbit in BC20 now. Transmission peaking at ~90%.
text: High shot-to-shot jitter really hinders the diagnostic utility of the toroids...

title: SWING SHIFT SUMMARY
text:
Comment # Comment 1LCLS: Delivered 10.7 GeV / 9.8 KeV to XPP and MFX with 10 Hz 6.3 GeV / 870 eV secondary beam to TMO. Tuned up HXR beam to ~ 1 mJ. SXR beam was ~ 1.5 mJ. 2LCLS: Delivered 6.3 GeV / 870 eV beam to TMO for user checkout and delivery. 3LCLS: The dual energy SXR config was very jittery and unstable (>50% shot to shot jitter), so we took some time to convert it to a primary SXR config with the linac LEMed to the soft line energy. Tuned up to ~ 4 mJ. 4LCLS: Lost most of the S27 RF after LI27 Cr 2 PDU died. Recovered it by doing a PDU reset but it then failed again a few minutes later. Rebuilt config by taking all stations in LI27 off the beam. ~0.3 h downtime. 5FACET-II: Worked on linac tuning and transmission to dump until 2200 when 11-2 was turned off in preparation for klystron swap tomorrow.

title: If your OPI firefox's bookmarks disappeared, you can try the following steps:
text: 1. Get a terminal and run this command: [physics@opi11 ~/Desktop]$ top 2. Then check for any firefox running in the background that consumed ~99% of CPU. If you find one, then you can just kill it by running this command: [physics@opi11 ~/Desktop]$ killall firefox 3. Relaunch firefox from the taskbar or from the terminal and you should see the bookmarks again. Cheers.
